/*	********IMPORTANT********:

******** YOU MUST FOLLOW THIS INSTRUCTION TO SET UP SQL SERVER AGENT JOB WHICH WILL AUTOMATICALLY UPDATE THE NEWS'S STATUS IN REALTIME ********

1.  Right click on SQL Server Agent and select Start if you haven't started it.

2.  In Object Explorer, expand the SQL Server Agent node.
	Right-click Jobs and select New Job.

3.  General Tab:
+)	Set the Name of the job to be Update News Status.

   Step Tab:
+)  Click New... to create a step.
+)	In the New Job Step window:
+)	Set the Step Name to UpdateStatus.
+)	Set Type to Transact-SQL Script (T-SQL).
+)	Set the Database to VaccinationManagement.
+)	In the Command field, paste the script:


UPDATE News
SET [Status] = CASE 
    WHEN GETDATE() > ExpiryDate THEN 0  
    WHEN GETDATE() >= PostDate THEN 1 
    ELSE 0
END
WHERE ExpiryDate IS NOT NULL AND PostDate IS NOT NULL;


Click OK to save.

   Schedules Tab:
+)	Click New... to create a schedule.
+)	In the New Job Schedule window:
+)	Set the Name to Run Daily.
+)	Under Frequency, choose the Occurs to be daily and Recurs every 1 day.
+)	Under Daily Frequency, select the Occurs every 10 seconds.
+)  Keep the Duration unchanged

4. Right-click the job (Update News Status) and select Start Job at Step....

5. Test the job

6. You can check the job history in SQL Server Agent > Jobs > Right-click Job > View History to ensure the job is running without errors

*/

